post_text: We are proud of our Columbia High School Students, for coordinating a peaceful student protest today, against systemic racism and police brutality. Several hundred residents were present to listen to our Scholars share their reflections on the Social Justice Crisis gripping our nation. They were eloquent, poignant, and direct...expressing their anger, pain, and frustration. The crowd was silent as each speaker shared their 'truths' ...which reflect what many of us are feeling during these uncertain times. We are so proud of our young people for their bravery, strength, and resilience. #SOMSDFamily

post_text: For the first time, in 2020 the U.S. Census Bureau will accept responses online. The process will be quick and secure. You can respond to the census in less time than it takes to finish your morning coffee. You’ll still be able to respond by mail. To learn more about what to expect, visit 2020census.gov. #2020Census

post_text: Over the last 3 days 500 people dropped off food to the Parenting Center's food insecurity initiative (@Morrow Church) and in the last 2 days we delivered packages of food to 175 families. Each package had 4 weeks worth of food (with an estimated $500 worth). Most importantly, thank you to all of our SOMA community who contributed to this initiative and to all our teachers, staff and interns who volunteered to deliver the food!
text: Over the last 3 days 500 people dropped off food to the Parenting Center's food insecurity initiative (@Morrow Church) and in the last 2 days we delivered packages of food to 175 families. Each package had 4 weeks worth of food (with an estimated $500 worth). Most importantly, thank you to all of our SOMA community who contributed to this initiative and to all our teachers, staff and interns who volunteered to deliver the food!

post_text: For our SOMSD families and students.
shared_text:
The College Board
March 16 at 12:29 PM ·

In response to the rapidly evolving situation around the coronavirus (COVID-19), the College Board is canceling the May 2, 2020, SAT administration. Makeup exams for the March 14 administration (scheduled March 28) are also canceled. Registered students will receive refunds.

The College Board will provide future additional SAT testing opportunities for students as soon as feasible in place of canceled administrations.

During this challenging time, our focus will remain on the health and safety of students. We will be flexible, thoughtful, and collaborative in exploring ways to continue to support student learning and provide opportunities to test.

More details: http://spr.ly/61861subu.
